### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 26](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 26:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 26:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#001.md), Saul, by the discovery of
the Ziphites, comes to Hachilah against David; [Sa1
26:4](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#004.md), David coming into the trench
stays Abishai from killing Saul, but takes his spear and cruse; [Sa1
26:13](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#013.md), David reproves Abner; [Sa1
26:17](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#017.md), and exhorts Saul; [Sa1
26:21](../../../bib/kjv/sa1026.htm#021.md), Saul acknowledges his sin.

